---
// Side-by-side pressure-time curves contrasting a light/fast bullet ("snap")
// against a heavy/slow bullet ("push") at equal Power Factor. The curve areas
// are drawn equal (same impulse = same momentum at equal PF); only the shape
// differs. Hand-tuned narrative visualization (not a measured curve).
---
<figure class="pcurves">
  <h3 class="pcurves-title">Pressure-time curves at 130 PF: same area, different shape</h3>

  <div class="pcurves-grid">
    <article class="pcurve amber">
      <header>
        <div class="pcurve-tag">115 gr · 1,130 fps</div>
        <div class="pcurve-verdict">SHORT, TALL · "Snap"</div>
      </header>
      <svg
        viewBox="0 0 400 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Pressure-time curve for a 115gr bullet at 1,130 fps (short, tall peak)"
        preserveAspectRatio="none"
      >
        {/* axes */}
        <line x1="30" y1="170" x2="380" y2="170" style="stroke: var(--border); stroke-width: 1;" />
        <line x1="30" y1="20"  x2="30"  y2="170" style="stroke: var(--border); stroke-width: 1;" />

        {/* axis labels. CSS custom properties only resolve inside style=,
           not in raw SVG presentation attributes. */}
        <text x="380" y="190" text-anchor="end" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--text-dim);">Time →</text>
        <text x="22"  y="22"  text-anchor="end" transform="rotate(-90 22 22)" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--text-dim);">Pressure ↑</text>

        {/* filled area */}
        <path
          d="M 80,170 C 130,170 150,50 180,50 C 210,50 230,170 280,170 Z"
          fill="rgba(245,158,11,0.20)"
          stroke="none"
        />
        {/* curve */}
        <path
          d="M 80,170 C 130,170 150,50 180,50 C 210,50 230,170 280,170"
          fill="none"
          style="stroke: var(--accent); stroke-width: 2.5; stroke-linecap: round;"
        />

        {/* peak marker */}
        <line x1="180" y1="50" x2="180" y2="170"
              stroke-dasharray="3,3"
              style="stroke: var(--accent); stroke-width: 1; opacity: 0.5;" />
        <circle cx="180" cy="50" r="3" style="fill: var(--accent);" />
        <text x="186" y="46" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; fill: var(--accent);">
          higher peak
        </text>
      </svg>
      <div class="pcurve-body">
        Light bullet at high velocity requires <strong>high peak pressure quickly</strong>. The
        pressure curve is tall and narrow. Recoil is delivered as a short, sharp spike: the
        gun jerks.
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="pcurve blue">
      <header>
        <div class="pcurve-tag">147 gr · 884 fps</div>
        <div class="pcurve-verdict">LONGER, LOWER · "Push"</div>
      </header>
      <svg
        viewBox="0 0 400 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Pressure-time curve for a 147gr bullet at 884 fps (wider, lower peak)"
        preserveAspectRatio="none"
      >
        <line x1="30" y1="170" x2="380" y2="170" style="stroke: var(--border); stroke-width: 1;" />
        <line x1="30" y1="20"  x2="30"  y2="170" style="stroke: var(--border); stroke-width: 1;" />

        <text x="380" y="190" text-anchor="end" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--text-dim);">Time →</text>
        <text x="22"  y="22"  text-anchor="end" transform="rotate(-90 22 22)" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--text-dim);">Pressure ↑</text>

        {/* filled area: wider, lower */}
        <path
          d="M 40,170 C 100,170 140,90 180,90 C 220,90 260,170 320,170 Z"
          fill="rgba(59,130,246,0.20)"
          stroke="none"
        />
        <path
          d="M 40,170 C 100,170 140,90 180,90 C 220,90 260,170 320,170"
          fill="none"
          style="stroke: var(--blue); stroke-width: 2.5; stroke-linecap: round;"
        />

        <line x1="180" y1="90" x2="180" y2="170"
              stroke-dasharray="3,3"
              style="stroke: var(--blue); stroke-width: 1; opacity: 0.5;" />
        <circle cx="180" cy="90" r="3" style="fill: var(--blue);" />
        <text x="186" y="86" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; fill: var(--blue);">
          lower peak
        </text>
      </svg>
      <div class="pcurve-body">
        Heavy bullet at lower velocity can be driven by <strong>lower peak pressure sustained
        longer</strong>. Same total impulse (same PF), but spread wider. The gun pushes,
        rather than snaps.
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="pcurves-foot">
    Area under each curve = impulse = total momentum. At equal Power Factor, the two areas are
    equal: only the shape differs. The hand integrates force over time but is most sensitive
    to peak force. A 15–30% shorter impulse with the same total momentum implies a 15–30% higher
    peak force, which is why the lighter bullet feels harder even when the math is nearly
    identical.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .pcurves {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin: 28px 0;
  }
  .pcurves-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .pcurves-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .pcurve {
    background: var(--bg-card-alt);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--border);
    padding: 16px 18px 18px;
  }
  .pcurve.amber { border-top-color: var(--accent); }
  .pcurve.blue  { border-top-color: var(--blue); }
  .pcurve header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .pcurve-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .pcurve.amber .pcurve-tag { color: var(--accent); }
  .pcurve.blue  .pcurve-tag { color: var(--blue); }
  .pcurve-verdict {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .pcurve svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 4px 0 12px;
  }
  .pcurve-body {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .pcurve-body strong { color: var(--text); }

  .pcurves-foot {
    margin-top: 18px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    background: var(--bg-card-alt);
    border-radius: 4px;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 850px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .pcurves { padding: 20px 16px; }
    .pcurves-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
